\slide{
\html-h1{The \tt{_BitInt} Debate \br \html-span[id=docnum]{P3639R0}}
}

\slide{
\slideh{Introduction}
C23 now has \tcode{_BitInt} type for N-bit integers (WG14 N2763, N2775):
\cppblock{
// 8-bit unsigned integer initialized with value 255.
// The literal suffix wb is unnecessary in this case.
unsigned _BitInt(8) x = 0xFFwb;
}
\ul{
\item{would be very useful in C++ for > 64-bit computation}
\item{\em{needs} to be in C++ to call C functions portably!}
\item{efforts to standardize in C++ abandoned (mainly N2763, P1889R1 (TS))}
\item{implemented by GCC and Clang; max: \tcode{_BitInt(8'388'608)}}
\item{\b{Big question}: fundamental type or class type in C++?}
}
}

